{"id": "ChIJfYSGw0fGwoARyMqh31EfoXg", "rating": 4.5, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_MODERATE", "userRatingCount": 1630, "displayName": {"text": "Marugame Monzo", "languageCode": "en"}, "editorialSummary": {"text": "Hip spot where an array of udon dishes are prepared with noodles hand-pulled in an open kitchen.", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJfYSGw0fGwoARyMqh31EfoXg/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGUVJ6UnJhV2xTUW04M1JWaElTRUZVT0ZkMWFGRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "Marugame Monzo definitely lives up to its reputation when it comes to udon — the noodles were genuinely very good, and I can see why so many people recommend the place. I ordered takeout, though, so I feel like the experience is probably much better when dining in. I tried the miso carbonara udon, and honestly, no regrets — it was rich, flavorful, and unique. That said, the portion size felt pretty small for the price, and overall it came across as quite overpriced for what you get. I enjoyed trying it once, but considering the cost and portion size, I probably wouldn’t go back.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Marugame Monzo definitely lives up to its reputation when it comes to udon — the noodles were genuinely very good, and I can see why so many people recommend the place. I ordered takeout, though, so I feel like the experience is probably much better when dining in. I tried the miso carbonara udon, and honestly, no regrets — it was rich, flavorful, and unique. That said, the portion size felt pretty small for the price, and overall it came across as quite overpriced for what you get. I enjoyed trying it once, but considering the cost and portion size, I probably wouldn’t go back.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Manja Petrov", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114983907554111844695/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI6ZNA6XGu7dWsbzCGnwsvDoOyyzyalHRAZnBXW4QlzCSyl6A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-23T19:45:21.749280723Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGUVJ6UnJhV2xTUW04M1JWaElTRUZVT0ZkMWFGRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tGUVJ6UnJhV2xTUW04M1JWaElTRUZVT0ZkMWFGRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c647c386847d:0x78a11f51dfa1cac8"}, {"name": "places/ChIJfYSGw0fGwoARyMqh31EfoXg/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21NelYwODNXR05hTVZjMU4wbGlXR3BSWVd4WWIzYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "A classic in the neighborhood. Their udon has a great texture to it, especially if served cold.\n\nGot the cold Ikura udon with grated radish, green onions, seaweed, and broth served on the side. It was refreshing, the broth was salty yet served in a small potion so it wasn’t overwhelming. The Ikura was fresh and zesty.\n\nTheir tempura appetizer was a great crunchy addition to how soft, salty and chewy the udon noodles were.\n\nThe only drawback is that when it gets busy, a divider is put between tables, so there’s no privacy and you overhear conversations. Would recommend coming here when it’s more chill. Overall, would recommend for great udon with great texture.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "A classic in the neighborhood. Their udon has a great texture to it, especially if served cold.\n\nGot the cold Ikura udon with grated radish, green onions, seaweed, and broth served on the side. It was refreshing, the broth was salty yet served in a small potion so it wasn’t overwhelming. The Ikura was fresh and zesty.\n\nTheir tempura appetizer was a great crunchy addition to how soft, salty and chewy the udon noodles were.\n\nThe only drawback is that when it gets busy, a divider is put between tables, so there’s no privacy and you overhear conversations. Would recommend coming here when it’s more chill. Overall, would recommend for great udon with great texture.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Matty Lee", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113770842502801175185/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1rAnA7ntdSbQ-QYLuJ7Dl2ni7bEbXmgACqyPLyQLGUX_qFugy=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-17T09:44:40.637896743Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21NelYwODNXR05hTVZjMU4wbGlXR3BSWVd4WWIzYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21NelYwODNXR05hTVZjMU4wbGlXR3BSWVd4WWIzYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c647c386847d:0x78a11f51dfa1cac8"}, {"name": "places/ChIJfYSGw0fGwoARyMqh31EfoXg/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tSYVpEQk9OV1pHUTJsWk9HRllSemxwU1daS1gwRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Small udon restaurant that has a Michelin star. Absolutely delicious udon. Loved their seafood curry udon. My husband got a broth udon that he loved. The staff is super friendly and welcoming. Can’t wait to come back and try another dish.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Small udon restaurant that has a Michelin star. Absolutely delicious udon. Loved their seafood curry udon. My husband got a broth udon that he loved. The staff is super friendly and welcoming. Can’t wait to come back and try another dish.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Marce M", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103384598039649927653/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHnLpbqocvZvWphk-SWcS2VV7J8YrqpLg7AanIATlMiOHdSA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-14T12:21:54.914173511Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tSYVpEQk9OV1pHUTJsWk9HRllSemxwU1daS1gwRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tSYVpEQk9OV1pHUTJsWk9HRllSemxwU1daS1gwRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c647c386847d:0x78a11f51dfa1cac8"}, {"name": "places/ChIJfYSGw0fGwoARyMqh31EfoXg/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25aMWVYZFZOMlpNTkhGTVFYSTFWbEJXUW1VemRWRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 3, "text": {"text": "Came here with my friend at 3:30pm on a Wednesday; honestly the perfect time because it was empty and service was great. I’d come back to try the creamy options, but this visit was a bit of a mixed bag.\n\nBeef with Fluffy Jidori Egg Udon (Double Portion) — 3/5 I’m used to the beef udon at places like Marugame where you get that sweet marinated meat and plenty of broth. I expected the egg to just be an accompaniment (like a soft-boiled egg you add on top), but this was different. The \"fluffy egg\" was more of a scrambled-boiled style that mixed in and turned the broth into a thick, creamy sauce.\n\nThe Issue: It was barely a soup. The egg sucked up all the liquid, and there wasn't even enough \"soup\" for one person, let alone the double portion of noodles we ordered. I was honestly pretty upset because I really wanted a noodle soup. We had to pay $2 extra for a side of dashi just to fix the dish ourselves, which shouldn't really happen. Once we fixed the broth level, the flavor of the beef and egg was yummy, and the dish was great, but I’d probably just stick to the regular beef udon next time.\n\nThe Noodles: The udon is super thick and very chewy. I personally prefer my noodles to be a bit more flour-based, but if you like a heavy chew, you’ll love these.\n\nMixed Tempura — 5/5 No complaints here! The batter was so nice, light, and crispy. Totally delightful.\n\nThe Spot: Shared the double portion and tempura and it was the perfect amount for two people who aren't starving. Just be careful with the egg dishes if you actually want broth!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Came here with my friend at 3:30pm on a Wednesday; honestly the perfect time because it was empty and service was great. I’d come back to try the creamy options, but this visit was a bit of a mixed bag.\n\nBeef with Fluffy Jidori Egg Udon (Double Portion) — 3/5 I’m used to the beef udon at places like Marugame where you get that sweet marinated meat and plenty of broth. I expected the egg to just be an accompaniment (like a soft-boiled egg you add on top), but this was different. The \"fluffy egg\" was more of a scrambled-boiled style that mixed in and turned the broth into a thick, creamy sauce.\n\nThe Issue: It was barely a soup. The egg sucked up all the liquid, and there wasn't even enough \"soup\" for one person, let alone the double portion of noodles we ordered. I was honestly pretty upset because I really wanted a noodle soup. We had to pay $2 extra for a side of dashi just to fix the dish ourselves, which shouldn't really happen. Once we fixed the broth level, the flavor of the beef and egg was yummy, and the dish was great, but I’d probably just stick to the regular beef udon next time.\n\nThe Noodles: The udon is super thick and very chewy. I personally prefer my noodles to be a bit more flour-based, but if you like a heavy chew, you’ll love these.\n\nMixed Tempura — 5/5 No complaints here! The batter was so nice, light, and crispy. Totally delightful.\n\nThe Spot: Shared the double portion and tempura and it was the perfect amount for two people who aren't starving. Just be careful with the egg dishes if you actually want broth!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Kat C", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104432535245037227957/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGhKzxHWkKzn3pUyVmBFHEiSoZfYoHH_Pc0p6pjvl_tWdWEA0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-30T12:54:32.940510658Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25aMWVYZFZOMlpNTkhGTVFYSTFWbEJXUW1VemRWRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25aMWVYZFZOMlpNTkhGTVFYSTFWbEJXUW1VemRWRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c647c386847d:0x78a11f51dfa1cac8"}, {"name": "places/ChIJfYSGw0fGwoARyMqh31EfoXg/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25kUVFsY3dNRGRhVWtaa1UyTndOWGhQYXpobFJHYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "Great Udon noodles just the portions might be small for some people. Ordered the Bukkake Udon and the Mentai Cream Udon, both were delicious.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Great Udon noodles just the portions might be small for some people. Ordered the Bukkake Udon and the Mentai Cream Udon, both were delicious.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jack", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104758513541530432398/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKIA6BHCQ7i-8NLtQUesUQG_81-q6GNG9XdN8GAhplREydwA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-09T08:15:12.986704664Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25kUVFsY3dNRGRhVWtaa1UyTndOWGhQYXpobFJHYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25kUVFsY3dNRGRhVWtaa1UyTndOWGhQYXpobFJHYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c647c386847d:0x78a11f51dfa1cac8"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJfYSGw0fGwoARyMqh31EfoXg/photos/AWCwydgXnrWIJpxdzP_gACOPo2S453QH6R5aYV90mrbnCyUGcGBOSHeai9upJ7MMZ1iyPM9rh_1TLvuXfnFQg3nKURY6nbrbVFW0G0Wv6gPnR3uWNA_EBwTFpy8vuOQhCpTiDIl-Q5-te6jehLk1iflbhmksHGNLIdHXWfgJq__92uGd6WnsGVLSnqfzPK_sYeHSYdENcedas7Wtgw3ubFl6tp7imgM74ZIXPcaAmTFnGE8OHBnt_JXvyI2PM-Kzq4FWfazJTuJLoLj7xjdDUlWbkykLLAzAsN5lxhcuchtBu9rXrgrekjjIjyufKUUAjE2iQSP0nldrFzSPVv3k2M8slWl8gRFTUCcRGEaJ5IoButsnEj2u-FvRUEUYwMTImf7NITUzXxJt5gFiH4SmfBuIxQnkmZ_opRqAKUn0ZeC3Z1SkBfE", 